# Concept Index

> Hash table mapping concepts to vault notes. Layer 1 of the Engram retrieval system.
> This file enables O(1) lookup: the agent searches here FIRST before grep or semantic search.

## How to populate

1. **One entry per concept.** Each concept maps to one or more vault notes via `[[wikilinks]]`.
2. **Format:** `| concept keyword | [[Path/To/Note]] | brief description |`
3. **Include aliases** in the concept column for searchability (e.g., "gamification, gamificacao").
4. **Cover all domains:** people, projects, research topics, tools, strategies.
5. **Update when:** creating new notes, renaming notes, archiving notes.
6. **Negative space matters:** if a concept is NOT in this index, the retrieval system escalates to Layer 2 (grep). Keep this index comprehensive to avoid unnecessary grep calls.

## Index

| Concept | Note | Description |
|---------|------|-------------|
| _example: your-concept_ | _[[Path/To/Your Note]]_ | _Brief description of what this note covers_ |

